name: Eldegoss
flavor_text: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

name: Applin
flavor_text: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.

name: Dipplin
evolves_into: Evolves from Applin and into Hydrapple ex
flavor_text: The head sticking out belongs to the fore-wyrm, while the tail belongs to the core-wyrm. The two share one apple and help each other out.

name: Nymble
flavor_text: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Lokix
flavor_text: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.

name: Toedscool
flavor_text: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

name: Toedscruel
flavor_text: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

name: Ponyta
evolves_into: Evolves into Rapidash or Dark Rapidash
flavor_text: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parent. It runs in fields and mountains all day.

name: Rapidash
flavor_text: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

name: Pansear
flavor_text: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Reshiram
flavor_text: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

name: Salandit
flavor_text: Only female Salandit can produce gas laden with pheromones. Males entranced by this gas will do whatever the females tell them.

name: Salazzle

name: Turtonator

name: Scorbunny

name: Raboot

name: Finneon

name: Lumineon

name: Tirtouga

name: Carracosta

name: Froakie

name: Frogadier

name: Chewtle

name: Drednaw

name: Veluza

name: Electabuzz

name: Electivire

name: Chinchou

name: Lanturn
flavor_text: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

name: Joltik

name: Vikavolt

name: Togedemaru

name: Zeraora

name: Pawmi

name: Drifloon
flavor_text: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a “signpost for wandering spirits.”

name: Drifblim
flavor_text: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can’t be a fixed destination.

name: Yamask

name: Comfey

name: Alcremie

name: Greavard
flavor_text: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.

name: Iron Boulder
flavor_text: It was named after a mysterious object recorded in an old book. Its body seems to be metallic.

name: Cubone
flavor_text: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

name: Marowak
flavor_text: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

name: Rhyhorn
flavor_text: Once it starts running, it won’t stop—even if it crashes through boulders. This disposition is what’s caused its habitat to expand.

name: Rhydon

flavor_text: It evolved to walk using only its hind legs, which has allowed it to expand its habitat even onto steep mountains.

name: Rhyperior
flavor_text: A Rhyperior’s brain is smaller than a Rhydon’s, but the Rhyperior is stronger because it spends more energy on battling and less on brainpower.

name: Meditite
evolves_into: Evolves into Medicham or Medicham ex
flavor_text: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.

name: Meditite
evolves_into: Evolves into Medicham or Medicham ex
flavor_text: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

name: Medicham

name: Pancham

name: Diancie
flavor_text: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

flavor_text: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.

name: Horsea

name: Seadra

name: Hypno
flavor_text: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.

name: Duskull
evolves_into: Evolves into Dusclops or Dusclops ex
flavor_text: Duskull’s victims suffer an intense chill as the Pokémon siphons their life-force away, glaring at them with its bright red eye all the while.

name: Dusclops
evolves_into: Evolves from Duskull and into Dusknoir
flavor_text: Dusclops’s true form is said to be a bright red eye burning within its body, but no one has ever seen such a thing.

name: Dusknoir
flavor_text: It comes and goes between this world and the afterlife. People fear this Pokémon because it is said to suck in lost spirits and take them along.

name: Cresselia
flavor_text: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Sylveon
flavor_text: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, but its piercing moves aim straight for its opponents’ weak spots.

name: Croagunk
evolves_into: Evolves into Toxicroak or Toxicroak ex
flavor_text: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.

name: Toxicroak
flavor_text: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.

name: Bloodmoon Ursaluna
flavor_text: This special Ursaluna can see in the dark with its left eye and protects itself with mud that is as hard as iron.

name: Slither Wing
flavor_text: This mysterious Pokémon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.

name: Zubat
evolves_into: Evolves into Golbat or Dark Golbat

name: Golbat
evolves_into: Evolves from Zubat and into Crobat or Crobat ex
flavor_text: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

name: Crobat
flavor_text: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target’s neck.

name: Absol
flavor_text: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

name: Zorua
flavor_text: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

name: Zoroark
flavor_text: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

name: Inkay
flavor_text: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

name: Malamar
flavor_text: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar’s control.

name: Yveltal

name: Kyurem
flavor_text: Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound.

evolves_into: Evolves into Persian, Dark Persian, or Persian-GX
flavor_text: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines, too.

name: Persian

name: Tangrowth

name: Pinsir
flavor_text: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Spinarak
flavor_text: Some fishers weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

name: Ariados
flavor_text: It wanders in search of food after darkness falls, never nesting in a specific place.

name: Sunkern
flavor_text: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.

name: Sunflora
flavor_text: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.

name: Heracross
flavor_text: With its herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

name: Volbeat
flavor_text: It flashes the light on its rear to communicate with other Volbeat. It loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

name: Illumise
flavor_text: It guides Volbeat to draw signs in the night sky. There are scholars who research the meaning of these signs.

name: Leafeon
flavor_text: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.

name: Phantump
flavor_text: This Pokémon came to be when the spirit of a deceased child possessed a tree stump. It now wanders the forest searching for friends.

name: Trevenant
evolves_into: Evolves from Phantump and into Trevenant BREAK
flavor_text: Trevenant is very kind to Pokémon living in the forest. It doesn’t even care if these Pokémon take up residence in the greenery on its head.

name: Grookey
flavor_text: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

name: Thwackey
evolves_into: Evolves from Grookey and into Rillaboom
flavor_text: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

name: Rillaboom
flavor_text: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: Applin
flavor_text: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.

name: Dipplin
evolves_into: Evolves from Applin and into Hydrapple ex
flavor_text: The head sticking out belongs to the fore-wyrm, while the tail belongs to the core-wyrm. The two share one apple and help each other out.

name: Iron Leaves
flavor_text: According to the few eyewitness accounts that exist, it used its shining blades to julienne large trees and boulders.

name: Poltchageist
evolves_into: Evolves into Sinistcha ex or Sinistcha
flavor_text: Poltchageist looks like a regional form of Sinistea, but it was recently discovered that the two Pokémon are entirely unrelated.

name: Poltchageist

flavor_text: Poltchageist looks like a regional form of Sinistea, but it was recently discovered that the two Pokémon are entirely unrelated.

name: Sinistcha
flavor_text: It prefers cool, dark places, such as the back of a shelf or the space beneath a home’s floorboards. It wanders in search of prey after sunset.

name: Sinistcha ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Teal Mask Ogerpon
flavor_text: This mischief-loving Pokémon is full of curiosity. It battles by drawing out the type-based energy contained within its masks.

name: Teal Mask Ogerpon ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Vulpix
evolves_into: Evolves into Ninetales, Ninetales ex, or Light Ninetales
flavor_text: As its body grows larger, its six warm tails become more beautiful, with a more luxurious coat of fur.

name: Ninetales
flavor_text: It has nine long tails and fur that gleams gold. It is said to live for 1,000 years.

name: Slugma
evolves_into: Evolves into Magcargo or Magcargo ex
flavor_text: It’s said that in ancient times, when volcanoes were more active, there were many more Slugma than there are now.

name: Magcargo ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Torkoal
flavor_text: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.

name: Chimchar
flavor_text: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

name: Monferno
evolves_into: Evolves from Chimchar and into Infernape
flavor_text: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

name: Infernape
flavor_text: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

name: Darumaka
flavor_text: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokémon will immediately fall asleep.

name: Darmanitan
flavor_text: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

name: Litwick
flavor_text: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life-force of any who follow it.

name: Lampent
evolves_into: Evolves from Litwick and into Chandelure
flavor_text: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.

name: Chandelure
flavor_text: It absorbs spirits, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: Chi-Yu
flavor_text: The envy accumulated within curved beads that sparked multiple conflicts has clad itself in fire and become a Pokémon.

name: Hearthflame Mask Ogerpon ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Poliwag
flavor_text: Its legs are newly grown, and it can’t walk very well. It seems to prefer swimming through the water instead.

name: Poliwhirl
evolves_into: Evolves from Poliwag and into Poliwrath
flavor_text: Its skin is moist all over its body. The skin on its belly spiral also feels smooth.

name: Poliwrath
flavor_text: It can use its well-developed arms and legs to run on the surface of the water for a split second.

name: Goldeen
flavor_text: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

name: Seaking
flavor_text: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

name: Jynx
flavor_text: In certain parts of Galar, Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.

name: Corphish
flavor_text: It can live in impure water, where it doesn’t need to compete with other water Pokémon for food, so its numbers have steadily increased.

name: Crawdaunt
flavor_text: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

name: Feebas
evolves_into: Evolves into Milotic or Milotic ex
flavor_text: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms schools and lives at the bottom of rivers that teem with plant life.

name: Milotic
flavor_text: It lives at the bottom of clear lakes. In times of war, it shows itself, which soothes people’s minds and hearts.

name: Snorunt
flavor_text: It is said that a home visited by a Snorunt will prosper. It can withstand cold of −150 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Glalie
flavor_text: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.

name: Froslass
flavor_text: It freezes prey by blowing its −58 degree Fahrenheit breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

name: Glaceon
flavor_text: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

name: Phione
flavor_text: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

name: Froakie
flavor_text: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

name: Frogadier
evolves_into: Evolves from Froakie and into Greninja or Greninja ex
flavor_text: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Cramorant
flavor_text: It’s an incredibly poor learner because it uses the bare minimum amount of energy for its brain. It focuses on battling instead.

name: Finizen
evolves_into: Evolves into Palafin or Palafin ex
flavor_text: Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that Finizen secretes from its blowhole.

name: Palafin
flavor_text: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen’s, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.

name: Palafin ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Iron Bundle
flavor_text: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.

name: Walking Wake
flavor_text: This ferocious creature is shrouded in mystery. It’s named after an aquatic monster mentioned in an old expedition journal.

name: Wellspring Mask Ogerpon ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Zapdos
flavor_text: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.

name: Shinx
flavor_text: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it’s in trouble.

name: Luxio
evolves_into: Evolves from Shinx and into Luxray or Luxray ex
flavor_text: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.

name: Luxray ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Emolga
flavor_text: As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can cause a lot of trouble.

name: Helioptile
flavor_text: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon’s electric moves.

name: Heliolisk
flavor_text: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

name: Morpeko
flavor_text: It has a small stomach. If it isn’t constantly eating the seeds it keeps in its pockets, it will get hungry immediately.

name: Tadbulb
flavor_text: It floats using the electricity stored in its body. When thunderclouds are around, Tadbulb will float higher off the ground.

name: Bellibolt
flavor_text: What appear to be eyeballs are actually organs for discharging the electricity generated by Bellibolt’s belly-button dynamo.

name: Wattrel
flavor_text: These Pokémon make their nests on coastal cliffs. The nests have a strange, crackling texture, and they’re a popular delicacy.

name: Kilowattrel
flavor_text: It uses its throat sac to store electricity generated by its wings. There’s hardly any oil in its feathers, so it is a poor swimmer.

name: Iron Thorns ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Clefairy
evolves_into: Evolves into Clefable or Clefable ex
flavor_text: On nights with a full moon, they gather together and dance. The surrounding area is enveloped in an abnormal magnetic field.

name: Clefable
flavor_text: It has an acute sense of hearing. It can easily hear a pin being dropped nearly 1,100 yards away.

name: Abra
flavor_text: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

name: Kadabra
evolves_into: Evolves from Abra and into Alakazam or Alakazam ex
flavor_text: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

name: Alakazam
flavor_text: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

name: Girafarig
evolves_into: Evolves into Farigiraf or Farigiraf ex
flavor_text: Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.

name: Farigiraf
flavor_text: The hardened head from the tail protects the head of the main body as Farigiraf whips its long neck around to headbutt enemies.

name: Chimecho
flavor_text: Its cries echo inside its hollow body to emerge as beautiful notes for startling and repelling foes.

name: Flabébé
flavor_text: This Flabébé rides a red flower. Immediately after birth, this Pokémon begins flying around in search of a flower it likes.

name: Floette
evolves_into: Evolves from Flabébé and into Florges
flavor_text: This Pokémon uses red wavelengths of light to pour its own energy into flowers and draw forth their latent potential.

name: Florges
flavor_text: They say that flower gardens created by Florges are constantly showered with a power that can heal both body and spirit.

name: Swirlix
flavor_text: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn’t get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.

name: Slurpuff
flavor_text: By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

name: Sandygast
flavor_text: It flings sand into the eyes of its prey and tries to close in on them while they’re blinded, but since Sandygast is so slow, the prey tends to escape.

name: Palossand
flavor_text: From the hollows in its arms, it fires the bones of its victims, which are all dried up after being drained of their vitality.

name: Enamorus
flavor_text: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon’s love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

flavor_text: Munkidori keeps itself somewhere safe while it toys with its foes, using psychokinesis to induce intense dizziness.

name: Fezandipiti
flavor_text: Fezandipiti beats its glossy wings to scatter pheromones that captivate people and Pokémon.

name: Sandshrew
flavor_text: No matter how high a place it falls from, this Pokémon can save itself by rolling into a ball and bouncing.

name: Sandslash
flavor_text: The spikes on its body are made up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.

name: Hisuian Growlithe
flavor_text: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.

name: Hisuian Arcanine
flavor_text: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

name: Nosepass
flavor_text: When endangered, it may protect itself by increasing its magnetism and drawing nearby iron objects to its body.

name: Probopass
flavor_text: Probopass radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances are rendered useless while it’s around.

name: Timburr
flavor_text: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle heavy lumber without difficulty.

name: Gurdurr
evolves_into: Evolves from Timburr and into Conkeldurr
flavor_text: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: Conkeldurr
flavor_text: Rather than rely on their strength, they master moves that make good use of centrifugal force to swing around concrete.

name: Greninja ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Hawlucha
flavor_text: Hawlucha live quietly without flocking together. They fight constantly with their natural enemies: noisy groups of Primeape.

name: Glimmet
evolves_into: Evolves into Glimmora ex or Glimmora
flavor_text: Glimmet’s toxic mineral crystals look just like flower petals. This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder like pollen to protect itself.

name: Glimmora
flavor_text: Glimmora’s petals are made of crystallized poison energy. It has recently become evident that these petals resemble Tera Jewels.

name: Ting-Lu
flavor_text: It slowly brings its exceedingly heavy head down upon the ground, splitting the earth open with huge fissures that run over 160 feet deep.

name: Okidogi
flavor_text: Okidogi is a ruffian with a short temper. It can pulverize anything by swinging around the chain on its neck.

name: Cornerstone Mask Ogerpon ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Poochyena
evolves_into: Evolves into Mightyena or Mightyena ex
flavor_text: Poochyena pursue their prey in packs. Once the prey is exhausted, the pack finishes it off. But sometimes the prey retaliates, and the pack flees.

name: Mightyena
flavor_text: Once it’s caught the scent of faraway prey, the leader gives a signal, and the whole pack moves out.

name: Venipede
flavor_text: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species, but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.

name: Whirlipede
evolves_into: Evolves from Venipede and into Scolipede
flavor_text: This Pokémon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.

name: Scolipede
flavor_text: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws’ toxic spikes.

name: Brute Bonnet
flavor_text: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokémon.

name: Skarmory
flavor_text: People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

name: Aron
flavor_text: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

name: Lairon
evolves_into: Evolves from Aron and into Aggron
flavor_text: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokémon often came into conflict with humans in the past.

name: Aggron
flavor_text: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.

name: Heatran
flavor_text: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Varoom
evolves_into: Evolves into Revavroom or Revavroom ex
flavor_text: The steel section is Varoom’s actual body. This Pokémon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.

name: Revavroom
flavor_text: Revavroom viciously threatens others with the sound of its exhaust. It sticks its tongue out from its cylindrical mouth and sprays toxic fluids.

name: Applin
flavor_text: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.

name: Dipplin
evolves_into: Evolves from Applin and into Hydrapple ex
flavor_text: The head sticking out belongs to the fore-wyrm, while the tail belongs to the core-wyrm. The two share one apple and help each other out.

name: Dreepy
flavor_text: It has a habit of biting at Clauncher even though it doesn’t feed on them. This is said to be vestigial behavior from when Dreepy was alive.

name: Drakloak
evolves_into: Evolves from Dreepy and into Dragapult or Dragapult ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon stores up energy in its lungs, then shoots it out. It takes care of Dreepy and battles alongside them until they’re all grown up.

flavor_text: N/A

name: Tatsugiri
flavor_text: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

name: Farfetch’d
flavor_text: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

name: Chansey
evolves_into: Evolves into Blissey or Blissey ex
flavor_text: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.

name: Ambipom

name: Ducklett

flavor_text: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.

name: Infernape
flavor_text: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

name: Froslass
flavor_text: It freezes prey by blowing its −58 degree Fahrenheit breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

name: Phione
flavor_text: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

name: Cramorant
flavor_text: It’s an incredibly poor learner because it uses the bare minimum amount of energy for its brain. It focuses on battling instead.

name: Heliolisk
flavor_text: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

name: Wattrel
flavor_text: These Pokémon make their nests on coastal cliffs. The nests have a strange, crackling texture, and they’re a popular delicacy.

name: Chimecho
flavor_text: Its cries echo inside its hollow body to emerge as beautiful notes for startling and repelling foes.

evolves_into: Evolves into Scizor, Scizor-GX, […] Kleavor, Scizor ex, or Dark Scizor
flavor_text: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

name: Pineco
evolves_into: Evolves into Forretress, Forretress ex, or Dark Forretress
flavor_text: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.

name: Seedot
flavor_text: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

name: Nuzleaf
evolves_into: Evolves from Seedot and into Shiftry, Shiftry-GX, or Shiftry ex
flavor_text: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

name: Shiftry
flavor_text: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe’s mind and take preemptive action.

name: Shroomish
flavor_text: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

name: Breloom
flavor_text: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.

name: Roselia
flavor_text: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

name: Roserade
flavor_text: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

name: Turtwig
flavor_text: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

name: Grotle
evolves_into: Evolves from Turtwig and into Torterra or Torterra ex
flavor_text: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

name: Torterra ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Shaymin
flavor_text: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Cottonee
flavor_text: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

name: Whimsicott
flavor_text: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it’ll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

name: Deerling
flavor_text: Deerling have different scents depending on the season. In this form, Deerling have a softly sweet scent that lingers in the nose.

name: Sawsbuck
flavor_text: Sawsbuck in their Autumn Form are known for having very short tempers. The males fight each other incessantly.

name: Grubbin
flavor_text: Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

name: Dhelmise
flavor_text: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

name: Bramblin
flavor_text: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.

name: Brambleghast
flavor_text: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokémon will bury an entire town.

name: Scovillain ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Rellor
flavor_text: It rolls its mud ball around while the energy it needs for evolution matures. Eventually the time comes for it to evolve.

name: Rabsca
flavor_text: An infant sleeps inside the ball. Rabsca rolls the ball soothingly with its legs to ensure the infant sleeps comfortably.

name: Iron Leaves ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Ponyta
evolves_into: Evolves into Rapidash or Dark Rapidash
flavor_text: It can’t run properly when it’s newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

name: Rapidash
flavor_text: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

name: Slugma
evolves_into: Evolves into Magcargo, Magcargo ex, Magcargo-GX, or Dark Magcargo
flavor_text: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.

name: Magcargo
flavor_text: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

name: Victini
flavor_text: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Heatmor
flavor_text: There’s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

name: Litten
flavor_text: It spends even the smallest amount of downtime grooming its fur with its tongue. Loose fur gathers in its stomach and serves as fuel for fiery moves.

name: Torracat
evolves_into: Evolves from Litten and into Incineroar-GX, Incineroar, or Incineroar ex
flavor_text: In the midst of battle, the fire pouch on Torracat’s neck rings like a bell and produces stronger flames than usual.

name: Incineroar ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Turtonator
flavor_text: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

name: Sizzlipede
flavor_text: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: Centiskorch
flavor_text: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

name: Gouging Fire ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Totodile
evolves_into: Evolves into Croconaw or Dark Croconaw
flavor_text: It is small but rough and tough. It won’t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

name: Croconaw
evolves_into: Evolves from Totodile and into Feraligatr
flavor_text: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.

name: Feraligatr
flavor_text: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.

name: Carvanha
evolves_into: Evolves into Sharpedo or Sharpedo ex
flavor_text: It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.

name: Sharpedo
flavor_text: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

name: Keldeo
flavor_text: Keldeo has strengthened its resolve for battle, filling its body with power and changing its form.

name: Snom
flavor_text: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft, freshly fallen snow, so it will eat its way up a mountain, aiming for the peak.

name: Frosmoth
flavor_text: Frosmoth senses air currents with its antennae. It sends its scales drifting on frigid air, making them fall like snow.

name: Wiglett
evolves_into: Evolves into Wugtrio or Wugtrio ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

name: Finizen
evolves_into: Evolves into Palafin or Palafin ex
flavor_text: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

name: Palafin
flavor_text: This Pokémon’s ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.

name: Walking Wake ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Pikachu
evolves_into: Evolves into Raichu, Alolan Raichu, […] Raichu-GX, Dark Raichu, or Raichu ex
flavor_text: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.

name: Raichu
evolves_into: Evolves from Pikachu and into Raichu BREAK or Raichu LV.X
flavor_text: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.

name: Electabuzz
flavor_text: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

name: Electivire
flavor_text: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

name: Charjabug
evolves_into: Evolves from Grubbin and into Vikavolt or Vikavolt-GX
flavor_text: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

name: Vikavolt
flavor_text: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.

name: Zeraora
flavor_text: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.

name: Yamper
flavor_text: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

name: Boltund
flavor_text: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

name: Wugtrio ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Iron Hands
flavor_text: This Pokémon shares many similarities with Iron Hands, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.

name: Iron Thorns
flavor_text: Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as Iron Thorns.

name: Mr. Mime
flavor_text: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

name: Marill
evolves_into: Evolves into Azumarill or Light Azumarill
flavor_text: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.

name: Azumarill
flavor_text: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

name: Girafarig
evolves_into: Evolves into Farigiraf or Farigiraf ex
flavor_text: Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.

name: Latias
flavor_text: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

name: Bronzor
flavor_text: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor’s back contained a mysterious power.

name: Bronzong
evolves_into: Evolves from Bronzor and into Bronzong BREAK
flavor_text: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: Solosis
flavor_text: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

name: Duosion
evolves_into: Evolves from Solosis and into Reuniclus
flavor_text: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mile—but only if its two brains can agree with each other.

name: Reuniclus
flavor_text: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokémon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.

name: Elgyem
flavor_text: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

name: Beheeyem
evolves_into: Evolves from Elgyem and into Beheeyem BREAK
flavor_text: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.

name: Cutiefly
flavor_text: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. You can find Cutiefly hovering around Gossifleur, trying to get some of Gossifleur’s pollen.

name: Ribombee
flavor_text: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs’ effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.

name: Scream Tail
flavor_text: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokémon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.

name: Flutter Mane
flavor_text: This Pokémon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane, a creature mentioned in a certain book.

name: Iron Valiant
flavor_text: It’s possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.

name: Iron Valiant
flavor_text: It’s possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.

name: Iron Crown ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Meditite
evolves_into: Evolves into Medicham or Medicham ex
flavor_text: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

name: Medicham
flavor_text: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

name: Relicanth
flavor_text: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

name: Drilbur
flavor_text: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.

name: Excadrill
flavor_text: It’s not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill’s rampant digging.

name: Golett
flavor_text: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

name: Golurk
flavor_text: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

name: Rockruff
evolves_into: Evolves into Lycanroc, Lycanroc-GX, or Lycanroc ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Lycanroc
flavor_text: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

name: Mudbray
flavor_text: This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won’t dry out even if it’s exposed to the sun for a long time.

name: Mudsdale
flavor_text: This Pokémon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.

name: Rolycoly
flavor_text: On sunny days, Rolycoly will come out onto grassy plains and roll around. Then it will eat the grass that gets tangled in its wheel-like leg.

name: Carkol
evolves_into: Evolves from Rolycoly and into Coalossal
flavor_text: The temperature inside its body increases when it experiences strong emotions. It rolls around frantically while spewing flames.

name: Coalossal
flavor_text: To intimidate its opponents, Coalossal will vigorously shake its body, scattering coal from its smoldering back.

name: Great Tusk

name: Arbok

name: Gastly
evolves_into: Evolves into Haunter or Dark Haunter

name: Sableye

name: Metang

flavor_text: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.

name: Metagross

flavor_text: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

flavor_text: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

name: Chatot

flavor_text: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.

name: Minccino

name: Cinccino
flavor_text: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won’t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

name: Drampa
flavor_text: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

flavor_text: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

evolves_into: Evolves into Charmeleon or Dark Charmeleon

name: Charmeleon
evolves_into: Evolves from Charmander and into Charizard, Charizard ex, Charizard-GX, or Special Delivery Charizard
flavor_text: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

name: Magmar
flavor_text: These Pokémon’s bodies are constantly burning. Magmar are feared as one of the causes behind fires.

name: Magmortar
evolves_into: Evolves from Magmar and into Magmortar LV.X
flavor_text: Living in the crater of a volcano has caused this Pokémon’s body to resemble its environment— it has an organ similar to a magma chamber.

name: Numel
evolves_into: Evolves into Camerupt or Camerupt ex
flavor_text: Magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold, the magma hardens and slows it.

name: Camerupt
flavor_text: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

name: Heat Rotom
flavor_text: If the convection microwave oven is not working properly, then the Rotom inhabiting it will become lethargic.

name: Charcadet
evolves_into: Evolves into Armarouge, Armarouge ex, or Ceruledge
flavor_text: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Armarouge
flavor_text: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

name: Lapras
flavor_text: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.

name: Frigibax
flavor_text: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.

name: Pikachu
evolves_into: Evolves into Raichu, Alolan Raichu, […] Raichu-GX, Dark Raichu, or Raichu ex
flavor_text: ﻿When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Raichu
evolves_into: Evolves from Pikachu and into Raichu BREAK or Raichu LV.X
flavor_text: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

name: Chinchou
evolves_into: Evolves into Lanturn or Light Lanturn
flavor_text: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.

name: Lanturn
flavor_text: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

name: Kilowattrel
flavor_text: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

name: Exeggcute
evolves_into: Evolves into Exeggutor, Alolan Exeggutor, Alolan Exeggutor-GX, or Dark Exeggutor
flavor_text: These Pokémon get nervous when they’re not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

name: Exeggutor
flavor_text: When they work together, Exeggutor’s three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

name: Natu
flavor_text: Because its wings aren’t yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

name: Xatu
flavor_text: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.

name: Ralts
flavor_text: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

name: Kirlia
evolves_into: Evolves from Ralts and into Gardevoir, Gallade, Gardevoir ex, or Gardevoir-GX
flavor_text: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

name: Gardevoir ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Chimecho
flavor_text: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

name: Mime Jr.
flavor_text: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy’s movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!

name: Woobat
flavor_text: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.

name: Swoobat
flavor_text: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.

name: Cottonee
flavor_text: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.

name: Whimsicott
flavor_text: As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.

name: Dedenne
flavor_text: It’s small and its electricity-generating organ is not fully developed, so it uses its tail to absorb electricity from people’s homes and charge itself.

name: Mimikyu
flavor_text: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

name: Fidough
evolves_into: Evolves into Dachsbun or Dachsbun ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough’s breath induces fermentation in the Pokémon’s vicinity.

name: Dachsbun
flavor_text: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon’s body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.

name: Ceruledge
flavor_text: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.

name: Flittle
evolves_into: Evolves into Espathra or Espathra ex
flavor_text: Flittle’s toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon’s belly.

name: Greavard
evolves_into: Evolves into Houndstone or Houndstone ex
flavor_text: This friendly Pokémon doesn’t like being alone. Pay it even the slightest bit of attention, and it will follow you forever.

name: Houndstone
flavor_text: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn’t like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.

name: Gimmighoul
evolves_into: Evolves into Gholdengo ex or Gholdengo
flavor_text: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

name: Mankey
evolves_into: Evolves into Primeape or Dark Primeape
flavor_text: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.

name: Primeape
evolves_into: Evolves from Mankey and into Annihilape or Annihilape ex
flavor_text: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.

name: Annihilape
flavor_text: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.

name: Phanpy
evolves_into: Evolves into Donphan or Dark Donphan
flavor_text: This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud, it won’t be able to settle down unless it washes its body.

name: Donphan
flavor_text: Donphan is covered in tough hide, so even being hit by a car won’t faze this Pokémon. However, it is extremely susceptible to rain.

name: Barboach
flavor_text: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey’s location.

name: Clobbopus
flavor_text: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.

name: Grapploct
flavor_text: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.

name: Vileplume
flavor_text: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

name: Scyther
evolves_into: Evolves into Scizor, Scizor-GX, […] Kleavor, Scizor ex, or Dark Scizor
flavor_text: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

name: Hoppip
flavor_text: This Pokémon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.

name: Skiploom
evolves_into: Evolves from Hoppip and into Jumpluff
flavor_text: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon’s head.

name: Jumpluff
flavor_text: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.

name: Pineco
evolves_into: Evolves into Forretress, Forretress ex, or Dark Forretress
flavor_text: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn’t bother it.

name: Snover
flavor_text: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain’s lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

name: Abomasnow
flavor_text: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

name: Smoliv
flavor_text: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

name: Dolliv
evolves_into: Evolves from Smoliv and into Arboliva
flavor_text: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

name: Arboliva
flavor_text: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.

name: Toedscool
evolves_into: Evolves into Toedscruel or Toedscruel ex
flavor_text: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

name: Capsakid
evolves_into: Evolves into Scovillain or Scovillain ex
flavor_text: Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of Capsakid among their ingredients.

name: Scovillain
flavor_text: The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.

name: Rellor
flavor_text: This Pokémon creates a mud ball by mixing sand and dirt with psychic energy. It treasures its mud ball more than its own life.

name: Charmander
evolves_into: Evolves into Charmeleon or Dark Charmeleon
flavor_text: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Charmeleon
evolves_into: Evolves from Charmander and into Charizard, Charizard ex, Charizard-GX, or Special Delivery Charizard
flavor_text: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

name: Paldean Tauros
flavor_text: People call this kind of Tauros the Blaze Breed due to the hot air it snorts from its nostrils. Its three tails are intertwined.

name: Entei
flavor_text: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

name: Oricorio
flavor_text: This Pokémon is incredibly popular, possibly because its passionate dancing is a great match with the temperament of Paldean people.

name: Charcadet
evolves_into: Evolves into Armarouge, Armarouge ex, or Ceruledge
flavor_text: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Armarouge
flavor_text: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

name: Slowpoke
evolves_into: Evolves into Slowbro, Slowking, […] Dark Slowbro, Dark Slowking, Slowking ex, or Light Slowbro
flavor_text: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

name: Slowbro
flavor_text: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.

name: Staryu
flavor_text: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn’t bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

name: Starmie
evolves_into: Evolves from Staryu and into Starmie BREAK
flavor_text: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

name: Paldean Tauros
flavor_text: It swims by jetting water from its horns. The most notable characteristic of the Aqua Breed is its high body fat, which allows it to float easily.

name: Wiglett
evolves_into: Evolves into Wugtrio or Wugtrio ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

name: Wugtrio
flavor_text: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.

name: Finizen
evolves_into: Evolves into Palafin or Palafin ex
flavor_text: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

name: Palafin
flavor_text: This Pokémon’s ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.

name: Veluza
flavor_text: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.

name: Dondozo
flavor_text: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

name: Tatsugiri
flavor_text: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

name: Frigibax
flavor_text: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.

name: Arctibax
evolves_into: Evolves from Frigibax and into Baxcalibur
flavor_text: Arctibax freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.

name: Baxcalibur
flavor_text: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.

name: Pikachu
evolves_into: Evolves into Raichu, Alolan Raichu, […] Raichu-GX, Dark Raichu, or Raichu ex
flavor_text: ﻿When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Raichu
evolves_into: Evolves from Pikachu and into Raichu BREAK or Raichu LV.X
flavor_text: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

name: Voltorb
evolves_into: Evolves into Electrode, Electrode-GX, Dark Electrode, or Electrode ex
flavor_text: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Electrode
flavor_text: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

name: Shinx
flavor_text: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

name: Luxio
evolves_into: Evolves from Shinx and into Luxray or Luxray ex
flavor_text: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

name: Luxray
evolves_into: Evolves from Luxio and into Luxray BREAK
flavor_text: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.

name: Pachirisu
flavor_text: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

name: Thundurus
flavor_text: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

name: Toxel
evolves_into: Evolves into Toxtricity, Toxtricity ex, or Light Toxtricity
flavor_text: It has no problem drinking dirty water. An organ inside Toxel’s body filters such water into a poisonous liquid that is harmless to Toxel.

name: Toxtricity
flavor_text: Many youths admire the way this Pokémon listlessly picks fights and keeps its cool no matter what opponent it faces.

name: Pawmi
flavor_text: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.

name: Pawmo
evolves_into: Evolves from Pawmi and into Pawmot or Pawmot ex
flavor_text: Pawmo uses a unique fighting technique in which it uses its forepaws to strike foes and zap them with electricity from its paw pads simultaneously.

name: Pawmot
flavor_text: Pawmot’s fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.

name: Wattrel
flavor_text: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

name: Kilowattrel
flavor_text: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

name: Wigglytuff
flavor_text: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.

name: Abra
evolves_into: Evolves into Kadabra or Dark Kadabra
flavor_text: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

name: Kadabra
evolves_into: Evolves from Abra and into Alakazam or Alakazam ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon’s telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.

name: Cleffa
flavor_text: Because of its unusual, starlike silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

name: Natu
flavor_text: Because its wings aren’t yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

name: Xatu
flavor_text: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.

name: Ralts
flavor_text: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

name: Kirlia
evolves_into: Evolves from Ralts and into Gardevoir, Gallade, Gardevoir ex, or Gardevoir-GX
flavor_text: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

name: Drifloon
flavor_text: It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

name: Drifblim
flavor_text: It can generate and release gas within its body. That’s how it can control the altitude of its drift.

name: Mime Jr.
flavor_text: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy’s movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!

name: Spiritomb
flavor_text: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

name: Klefki
flavor_text: In the past, noble families entrusted their vault keys to a Klefki. They passed the Klefki down through the generations, taking good care of it.

name: Mimikyu
flavor_text: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

name: Dachsbun
flavor_text: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon’s body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.

name: Ceruledge
flavor_text: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.

name: Rabsca
flavor_text: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokémon is actually inside the ball.

name: Flittle
evolves_into: Evolves into Espathra or Espathra ex
flavor_text: Flittle’s toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon’s belly.

name: Tinkatink
flavor_text: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

name: Tinkatuff
evolves_into: Evolves from Tinkatink and into Tinkaton or Tinkaton ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.

name: Tinkaton
flavor_text: This intelligent Pokémon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying Corviknight.

name: Houndstone
flavor_text: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn’t like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.

name: Mankey
evolves_into: Evolves into Primeape or Dark Primeape
flavor_text: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.

name: Primeape
evolves_into: Evolves from Mankey and into Annihilape or Annihilape ex
flavor_text: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.

name: Annihilape
flavor_text: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.

name: Paldean Tauros
flavor_text: This kind of Tauros, known as the Combat Breed, is distinguished by its thick, powerful muscles and its fierce disposition.

name: Riolu
evolves_into: Evolves into Lucario, Lucario-GX, or Lucario ex
flavor_text: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Lucario
evolves_into: Evolves from Riolu and into Lucario LV.X
flavor_text: It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.

name: Hawlucha
flavor_text: Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly leaping around using its wings—are polished in the forest where it was born and raised.

name: Nacli
flavor_text: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.

name: Naclstack
evolves_into: Evolves from Nacli and into Garganacl or Garganacl ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey’s body.

name: Garganacl
flavor_text: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.

name: Glimmet
evolves_into: Evolves into Glimmora ex or Glimmora
flavor_text: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.

name: Paldean Wooper
evolves_into: Evolves into Paldean Clodsire ex or Paldean Clodsire
flavor_text: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

name: Murkrow
flavor_text: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Sneasel
flavor_text: This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

name: Weavile
flavor_text: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.

name: Sableye
flavor_text: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

name: Pawniard
flavor_text: Pawniard will fearlessly challenge even powerful foes. In a pinch, it will cling to opponents and pierce them with the blades all over its body.

name: Bisharp
evolves_into: Evolves from Pawniard and into Kingambit
flavor_text: This Pokémon commands a group of several Pawniard. Groups that are defeated in territorial disputes are absorbed by the winning side.

name: Kingambit
flavor_text: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.

name: Mabosstiff
flavor_text: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.

name: Shroodle
evolves_into: Evolves into Grafaiai or Grafaiai ex
flavor_text: Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.

name: Grafaiai
flavor_text: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

name: Scizor
flavor_text: This Pokémon’s pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.

name: Varoom
evolves_into: Evolves into Revavroom or Revavroom ex
flavor_text: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

name: Revavroom
flavor_text: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders— now numbering eight—to generate energy.

name: Noibat
evolves_into: Evolves into Noivern, Noivern ex, or Noivern-GX
flavor_text: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from its large ears to search for fruit to eat. It mistakes Applin for its food.

name: Cyclizar
flavor_text: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

name: Pidgey
flavor_text: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Pidgeotto
evolves_into: Evolves from Pidgey and into Pidgeot or Pidgeot ex
flavor_text: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Jigglypuff
evolves_into: Evolves into Wigglytuff, Wigglytuff ex, […] Dark Wigglytuff, Light Wigglytuff, or Wigglytuff-GX
flavor_text: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

name: Doduo
flavor_text: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

name: Dodrio
flavor_text: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.

name: Ditto
flavor_text: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can’t maintain its disguise.

name: Snorlax
flavor_text: This Pokémon’s stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.

name: Wingull
flavor_text: It soars high in the sky, riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.

name: Pelipper
flavor_text: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.

name: Skwovet
evolves_into: Evolves into Greedent or Greedent ex
flavor_text: No matter how much it stuffs its belly with food, it is always anxious about getting hungry again. So, it stashes berries in its cheeks and tail.

name: Greedent
flavor_text: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.

name: Lechonk
evolves_into: Evolves into Oinkologne or Oinkologne ex
flavor_text: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn’t use it for anything other than foraging.

name: Oinkologne
flavor_text: This Pokémon sends a flowerlike scent wafting about. Well-developed muscles in its legs allow it to leap more than 16 feet with no trouble at all.

name: Tandemaus
evolves_into: Evolves into Maushold or Maushold ex
flavor_text: Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.

name: Maushold
flavor_text: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.

name: Flamigo
flavor_text: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

name: Surskit
flavor_text: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.

name: Masquerain
flavor_text: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.

flavor_text: N/A

name: Pansage
flavor_text: It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.

name: Simisage
flavor_text: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Dwebble
flavor_text: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

name: Crustle
flavor_text: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They’re mighty enough to crack Rhyperior’s carapace.

name: Bounsweet
flavor_text: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled- down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

name: Steenee
evolves_into: Evolves from Bounsweet and into Tsareena, Tsareena ex, or Tsareena-GX
flavor_text: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.

name: Blipbug
flavor_text: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

name: Dottler
evolves_into: Evolves from Blipbug and into Orbeetle
flavor_text: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

name: Orbeetle
flavor_text: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.

name: Nymble
flavor_text: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Nymble
flavor_text: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Toedscool
evolves_into: Evolves into Toedscruel or Toedscruel ex
flavor_text: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

name: Toedscool
evolves_into: Evolves into Toedscruel or Toedscruel ex
flavor_text: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

name: Toedscruel
flavor_text: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.

name: Wo-Chien
flavor_text: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.

name: Magby
flavor_text: This Pokémon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day, Magby soaks in magma, resting and recovering from the day’s fatigue.

name: Pansear
flavor_text: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Simisear
flavor_text: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

name: Volcanion
flavor_text: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

name: Fuecoco
flavor_text: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

name: Crocalor
evolves_into: Evolves from Fuecoco and into Skeledirge ex or Skeledirge
flavor_text: The combination of Crocalor’s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokémon’s head.

name: Charcadet
evolves_into: Evolves into Armarouge, Armarouge ex, or Ceruledge
flavor_text: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Charcadet
evolves_into: Evolves into Armarouge, Armarouge ex, or Ceruledge
flavor_text: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Armarouge ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Iron Moth
flavor_text: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.

name: Chi-Yu
flavor_text: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.

name: Horsea
flavor_text: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

name: Seadra
evolves_into: Evolves from Horsea and into Kingdra, Kingdra ex, or Kingdra-GX
flavor_text: Seadra’s mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that’s larger than the opening of its mouth.

name: Kingdra
flavor_text: Scales shed by this Pokémon have such a splendorous gleam to them that they’ve been given to royalty as gifts.

name: Remoraid
evolves_into: Evolves into Octillery or Dark Octillery
flavor_text: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine’s underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery
flavor_text: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

name: Feebas
evolves_into: Evolves into Milotic or Milotic ex
flavor_text: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.

name: Milotic
flavor_text: It’s said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you’re feeling.

name: Snorunt
