name: Venusaur ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Charmander
evolves_into: Evolves into Charmeleon or Dark Charmeleon
flavor_text: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Charmeleon
evolves_into: Evolves from Charmander and into Charizard, Charizard ex, Charizard-GX, or Special Delivery Charizard
flavor_text: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

name: Charizard ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Squirtle
evolves_into: Evolves into Wartortle or Dark Wartortle
flavor_text: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

name: Wartortle
evolves_into: Evolves from Squirtle and into Blastoise, Blastoise ex, or Blastoise-GX
flavor_text: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.

name: Blastoise ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Caterpie
flavor_text: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

name: Metapod
evolves_into: Evolves from Caterpie and into Butterfree
flavor_text: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can’t withstand a harsh attack.

name: Butterfree
flavor_text: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

name: Weedle
flavor_text: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

name: Kakuna
evolves_into: Evolves from Weedle and into Beedrill
flavor_text: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: Beedrill
flavor_text: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

name: Pidgey
flavor_text: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Pidgeotto
evolves_into: Evolves from Pidgey and into Pidgeot or Pidgeot ex
flavor_text: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Pidgeot
flavor_text: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.

name: Rattata
evolves_into: Evolves into Raticate or Dark Raticate
flavor_text: This Pokémon is common but hazardous. Its sharp incisors can easily cut right through hard wood.

name: Raticate
evolves_into: Evolves from Rattata and into Raticate BREAK
flavor_text: Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.

name: Spearow
flavor_text: Due to its short wings, it can’t fly long distances. It wanders about restlessly and pecks at bug Pokémon.

name: Fearow
flavor_text: Carrying food through Fearow’s territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!

name: Ekans
evolves_into: Evolves into Arbok, Dark Arbok, or Arbok ex
flavor_text: The eggs of bird Pokémon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints.

name: Arbok ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Pikachu
evolves_into: Evolves into Raichu, Alolan Raichu, […] Raichu-GX, Dark Raichu, or Raichu ex
flavor_text: ﻿When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Raichu
evolves_into: Evolves from Pikachu and into Raichu BREAK or Raichu LV.X
flavor_text: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

name: Sandshrew
evolves_into: Evolves into Sandslash or Dark Sandslash
flavor_text: It burrows into the ground to create its nest. If hard stones impede its tunneling, it uses its sharp claws to shatter them and then carries on digging.

name: Sandslash
flavor_text: It climbs trees by hooking on with its sharp claws. Sandslash shares the berries it gathers, dropping them down to Sandshrew waiting below the tree.

name: Nidoran Female
flavor_text: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran’s horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male’s horn.

name: Nidorina
evolves_into: Evolves from Nidoran Female and into Nidoqueen
flavor_text: If the group is threatened, these Pokémon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.

name: Nidoqueen
flavor_text: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

name: Nidoran Male
flavor_text: Small but brave, this Pokémon will hold its ground and even risk its life in battle to protect the female it’s friendly with.

name: Nidorino
evolves_into: Evolves from Nidoran Male and into Nidoking
flavor_text: It’s nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

name: Nidoking
evolves_into: Evolves from Nidorino and into Nidoking BREAK
flavor_text: Nidoking prides itself on its strength. It’s forceful and spirited in battle, making use of its thick tail and diamond-crushing horn.

name: Clefairy
evolves_into: Evolves into Clefable or Clefable ex
flavor_text: Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. However, this cute Pokémon is rarely found.

name: Clefable
flavor_text: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they’re usually found in quiet places.

name: Vulpix
evolves_into: Evolves into Ninetales, Ninetales ex, or Light Ninetales
flavor_text: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

name: Ninetales ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Jigglypuff
evolves_into: Evolves into Wigglytuff, Wigglytuff ex, […] Dark Wigglytuff, Light Wigglytuff, or Wigglytuff-GX
flavor_text: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

name: Wigglytuff ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Zubat
evolves_into: Evolves into Golbat or Dark Golbat
flavor_text: Zubat live in caves, down where the sun’s light won’t reach. In the morning, they gather together to keep each other warm as they sleep.

name: Golbat
evolves_into: Evolves from Zubat and into Crobat or Crobat ex
flavor_text: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokémon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.

name: Oddish
evolves_into: Evolves into Gloom or Dark Gloom
flavor_text: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

name: Gloom
evolves_into: Evolves from Oddish and into Vileplume, Bellossom, Vileplume-GX, or Vileplume ex
flavor_text: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

name: Vileplume
flavor_text: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

name: Paras
flavor_text: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

name: Parasect
flavor_text: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

name: Venonat
evolves_into: Evolves into Venomoth, Venomoth-GX, or Light Venomoth
flavor_text: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokémon at night that are attracted by light.

name: Venomoth
flavor_text: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

name: Diglett
evolves_into: Evolves into Dugtrio or Dark Dugtrio
flavor_text: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

name: Dugtrio
flavor_text: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

name: Meowth
evolves_into: Evolves into Persian, Dark Persian, or Persian-GX
flavor_text: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Persian
flavor_text: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

name: Psyduck
evolves_into: Evolves into Golduck, Dark Golduck, or Light Golduck
flavor_text: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

name: Golduck
evolves_into: Evolves from Psyduck and into Golduck BREAK
flavor_text: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.

name: Mankey
evolves_into: Evolves into Primeape or Dark Primeape
flavor_text: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

name: Primeape
evolves_into: Evolves from Mankey and into Annihilape or Annihilape ex
flavor_text: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

name: Growlithe
evolves_into: Evolves into Arcanine, Arcanine ex, or Light Arcanine
flavor_text: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine
evolves_into: Evolves from Growlithe and into Arcanine BREAK
flavor_text: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

name: Poliwag
flavor_text: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pokémon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.

name: Poliwhirl
evolves_into: Evolves from Poliwag and into Poliwrath, Politoed, or Politoed ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon’s sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies’ grasp and escape.

name: Poliwrath
flavor_text: Poliwrath is skilled at both swimming and martial arts. It uses its well-trained arms to dish out powerful punches.

name: Abra
evolves_into: Evolves into Kadabra or Dark Kadabra
flavor_text: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

name: Kadabra
evolves_into: Evolves from Abra and into Alakazam or Alakazam ex
flavor_text: This Pokémon’s telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.

name: Alakazam ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Machop
evolves_into: Evolves into Machoke, Dark Machoke, or Light Machoke
flavor_text: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.

name: Machoke
evolves_into: Evolves from Machop and into Machamp or Machamp-GX
flavor_text: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

name: Machamp
evolves_into: Evolves from Machoke and into Machamp BREAK or Machamp LV.X
flavor_text: With four arms that react more quickly than it can think, it can execute many punches at once.

name: Bellsprout
flavor_text: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

name: Weepinbell
evolves_into: Evolves from Bellsprout and into Victreebel
flavor_text: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

name: Victreebel
flavor_text: Once ingested into this Pokémon’s body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

name: Tentacool
flavor_text: This Pokémon is mostly made of water. A Tentacool out in the ocean is very hard to spot, because its body blends in with the sea.

name: Tentacruel
flavor_text: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and shrink freely. Tentacruel ensnares prey in a net of spread-out tentacles, delivering venomous stings to its catch.

name: Geodude
flavor_text: It uses both hands to climb precipitous cliffs. People who see it in action have been known to take up bouldering.

name: Graveler
evolves_into: Evolves from Geodude and into Golem or Golem ex
flavor_text: It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.

name: Golem ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Ponyta
evolves_into: Evolves into Rapidash or Dark Rapidash
flavor_text: If you’ve been accepted by Ponyta, its burning mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.

name: Rapidash
flavor_text: The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it decides the herd’s pace and direction of travel.

name: Slowpoke
evolves_into: Evolves into Slowbro, Slowking, […] Dark Slowbro, Dark Slowking, Slowking ex, or Light Slowbro
flavor_text: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

name: Slowbro
flavor_text: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

name: Magnemite
evolves_into: Evolves into Magneton or Dark Magneton
flavor_text: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Magneton
evolves_into: Evolves from Magnemite and into Magnezone or Magnezone ex
flavor_text: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

name: Farfetch’d
flavor_text: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

name: Doduo
flavor_text: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

name: Dodrio
flavor_text: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.

name: Seel
evolves_into: Evolves into Dewgong or Light Dewgong
flavor_text: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don’t bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

name: Dewgong
flavor_text: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.

name: Grimer
evolves_into: Evolves into Muk, Dark Muk, or Muk ex
flavor_text: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

name: Muk
flavor_text: It’s thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

name: Shellder
flavor_text: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

name: Cloyster
flavor_text: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

name: Gastly
evolves_into: Evolves into Haunter or Dark Haunter
flavor_text: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

name: Haunter
evolves_into: Evolves from Gastly and into Gengar or Gengar ex
flavor_text: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

name: Gengar
evolves_into: Evolves from Haunter and into Gengar LV.X
flavor_text: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey’s shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

name: Onix
evolves_into: Evolves into Steelix, Dark Steelix, or Steelix ex
flavor_text: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

name: Drowzee
evolves_into: Evolves into Hypno or Dark Hypno
flavor_text: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children’s are much tastier.

name: Hypno
flavor_text: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

name: Krabby
flavor_text: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

name: Kingler
flavor_text: Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it’s not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.

name: Voltorb
evolves_into: Evolves into Electrode, Electrode-GX, Dark Electrode, or Electrode ex
flavor_text: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Electrode
flavor_text: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

name: Exeggcute
evolves_into: Evolves into Exeggutor, Alolan Exeggutor, Alolan Exeggutor-GX, or Dark Exeggutor
flavor_text: These Pokémon get nervous when they’re not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

name: Exeggutor
flavor_text: When they work together, Exeggutor’s three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

name: Cubone
evolves_into: Evolves into Marowak, Alolan Marowak, Alolan Marowak-GX, or Dark Marowak
flavor_text: This Pokémon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone’s dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.

name: Marowak
evolves_into: Evolves from Cubone and into Marowak BREAK
flavor_text: When this Pokémon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak’s temperament also turned vicious at the same time.

name: Hitmonlee
flavor_text: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

name: Hitmonchan
flavor_text: Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.

name: Lickitung
flavor_text: Bug Pokémon are Lickitung’s main food source. This Pokémon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.

name: Koffing
evolves_into: Evolves into Weezing, Galarian Weezing, or Dark Weezing
flavor_text: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

name: Weezing
flavor_text: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.

name: Rhyhorn
flavor_text: It can remember only one thing at a time. Once it starts rushing, it forgets why it started.

name: Rhydon
evolves_into: Evolves from Rhyhorn and into Rhyperior
flavor_text: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Chansey
evolves_into: Evolves into Blissey or Blissey ex
flavor_text: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Tangela
flavor_text: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Kangaskhan ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Horsea
flavor_text: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

name: Seadra
evolves_into: Evolves from Horsea and into Kingdra, Kingdra ex, or Kingdra-GX
flavor_text: Seadra’s mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that’s larger than the opening of its mouth.

name: Goldeen
flavor_text: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

name: Seaking
flavor_text: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

name: Staryu
flavor_text: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn’t bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

name: Starmie
evolves_into: Evolves from Staryu and into Starmie BREAK
flavor_text: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

name: Mr. Mime
flavor_text: It’s known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.

name: Scyther
evolves_into: Evolves into Scizor, Scizor-GX, […] Kleavor, Scizor ex, or Dark Scizor
flavor_text: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

name: Jynx ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Electabuzz
flavor_text: With the coming of a storm, many of these Pokémon will gather under tall trees and sit there waiting for lightning to strike.

name: Magmar
flavor_text: These Pokémon’s bodies are constantly burning. Magmar are feared as one of the causes behind fires.

name: Pinsir
flavor_text: This Pokémon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

name: Tauros
flavor_text: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

name: Magikarp
evolves_into: Evolves into Gyarados, Gyarados-GX, Dark Gyarados, or Gyarados ex
flavor_text: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

name: Gyarados
flavor_text: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

name: Lapras
flavor_text: Crossing icy seas is no issue for this cold-resistant Pokémon. Its smooth skin is a little cool to the touch.

name: Ditto
flavor_text: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can’t maintain its disguise.

name: Eevee
evolves_into: Evolves into Jolteon, Flareon, […] Vaporeon, Umbreon, Espeon, Leafeon, Glaceon, Sylveon, Sylveon-GX, Glaceon-GX, Umbreon-GX, Leafeon-GX, Espeon-GX, Dark Vaporeon, Dark Espeon, Dark Flareon, Umbreon ex, Dark Jolteon, Jolteon ex, Jolteon-GX, Vaporeon ex, Espeon ex, Vaporeon-GX, Light Flareon, Light Jolteon, Flareon ex, Light Vaporeon, or Flareon-GX
flavor_text: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Vaporeon
flavor_text: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

name: Jolteon
flavor_text: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

name: Flareon
flavor_text: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
evolves_into: Evolves into Porygon2 or Dark Porygon2
flavor_text: In recent years, this species has been very helpful in cyberspace. These Pokémon will go around checking to make sure no suspicious data exists.

name: Omanyte
evolves_into: Evolves from Antique Helix Fossil and into Omastar
flavor_text: This Pokémon is a member of an ancient, extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles, looking like it’s just drifting along.

name: Omastar
evolves_into: Evolves from Omanyte and into Omastar BREAK
flavor_text: Omastar’s sharp fangs could crush rock, but the Pokémon can attack only the prey that come within reach of its tentacles.

name: Kabuto
evolves_into: Evolves from Antique Dome Fossil and into Kabutops or Kabutops ex
flavor_text: While some say this species has gone extinct, Kabuto sightings are apparently fairly common in some places.

name: Kabutops
flavor_text: The cause behind the extinction of this species is unknown. Kabutops were aggressive Pokémon that inhabited warm seas.

name: Aerodactyl
flavor_text: Aerodactyl’s sawlike fangs can shred skin to tatters—even the skin of Steel-type Pokémon.

name: Snorlax
flavor_text: This Pokémon’s stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.

name: Articuno
flavor_text: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

name: Zapdos ex
flavor_text: N/A

name: Moltres
flavor_text: There are stories of this Pokémon using its radiant, flame-cloaked wings to light up paths for those lost in the mountains.

name: Dratini
evolves_into: Evolves into Dragonair, Dark Dragonair, or Light Dragonair
flavor_text: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

name: Dragonair
evolves_into: Evolves from Dratini and into Dragonite, Dragonite-GX, or Dragonite ex
flavor_text: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

name: Dragonite
flavor_text: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.

name: Mewtwo
flavor_text: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

evolves_into: Evolves into Golduck, Dark Golduck, or Light Golduck
